# Binaries
bin/
/dist/
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test / coverage
*.test
*.out
coverage.txt
coverage.html
coverage.*

# Go workspace
go.work
go.work.sum

# Dev installs — a `vh-agent-harness install` into a scratch dir inside the repo during
# dev pulls npm deps under <target>/.opencode/node_modules. Ignore them so they
# never leak into commits.
node_modules/

# Dev junk
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak

# Local-only notes (sensitive; never commit)
*.local.md

# auto-classifier-pilot config files live under .opencode/repo-configs/.
# Three kinds, two ignore rules:
#   1. CONVENTION local-companions (gitignored): the optional `.local.json`
#      shallow field-override beside each committed base file. auto-gate is the
#      first consumer (auto-gate-config.local.json / auto-gate-llm.local.json).
#      The scoped wildcard keeps these per-developer and out of history without
#      over-matching files outside repo-configs/.
#   2. The SECRETS LLM file (gitignored): auto-gate-llm.json is NEVER committed
#      (secrets-adjacent — model endpoint/key). Only the LLM file is ignored by
#      its bare name; the behavior-config base (auto-gate-config.json) is NOT
#      ignored — it is the optionally-committable shared base.
#   3. COMMITTED base files (NOT gitignored): X.json files under repo-configs/
#      are intended to be committed when they encode shared project policy.
.opencode/repo-configs/*.local.json
.opencode/repo-configs/auto-gate-llm.json

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# Built binary at repo root (local `go build` output; never commit)
/vh-agent-harness

# Dev scratch / virtualenvs (build-root local; never commit)
.venv/
venv/
tmp/

# Throwaway dev tooling at repo root (e.g. tmp-tools/ proof harnesses). Kept on
# disk for local use but never committed / never part of the public module.
/tmp-*

# External reference repos cloned for local study (never commit)
refs/

# --- vh-agent-harness (self-hosted): runtime state (never commit) ---
.opencode/state/
.opencode/sessions/
.opencode/plans/
.opencode/runs/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.local/coordinator/
.local/config/
.opencode/node_modules/
